<paragraph id="537A36CFB537FFD9FF23FD4DFB0CFCB0" blockId="3.[136,1452,158,833]" pageId="3" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis id="61B1EADDB537FFD9FF23FD4DFDFCFD41" bold="true" box="[189,516,662,688]" pageId="3" pageNumber="113">Taxonomic relationships:—</emphasis>
According to the classification of 
<bibRefCitation id="37544B3EB537FFD9FCE9FD4CFC1FFD41" author="Lo, H. S." box="[887,999,662,689]" pageId="3" pageNumber="113" pagination="275 - 283" refId="ref2494" refString="Lo, H. S. (1998) Materials for Chinese Rubiaceae (IV). Bulletin of Botanical Research, Harbin 18: 275 - 283." type="journal article" year="1998">Lo (1998)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="94C54D4CB537FFD9FC6EFD4DFB32FD41" box="[1008,1226,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="3" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elliptica">
<emphasis id="61B1EADDB537FFD9FC6EFD4DFB32FD41" box="[1008,1226,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="113">Spiradiclis elliptica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="94C54D4CB537FFD9FF16FD61FEC8FD25" authorityName="H.S.Lo" authorityYear="1998" box="[136,304,698,724]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Sinospiradiclis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="3" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="61B1EADDB537FFD9FF16FD61FEC8FD25" box="[136,304,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="113">Sinospiradiclis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the subglobose capsules dehiscent with 4 valves when mature. This species is distinguishable from other species of the genus mainly by its large stipule and distinctive bract. To our knowledge, the bracts of the known species of 
<taxonomicName id="94C54D4CB537FFD9FECFFCD9FE32FCED" authorityName="Blume" authorityYear="1926" box="[337,458,770,796]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="3" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="61B1EADDB537FFD9FECFFCD9FE32FCED" box="[337,458,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="113">Spiradiclis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are described as linear or subulate (vs. oblong to ovate-oblong in 
<taxonomicName id="94C54D4CB537FFD9FB33FCD8FADDFCED" box="[1197,1317,770,797]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="3" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elliptica">
<emphasis id="61B1EADDB537FFD9FB33FCD8FADDFCED" box="[1197,1317,770,797]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="113">S. elliptica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the apices of which are lanceolate or acute (vs. rounded), and the color are green (vs. white or sometimes pink).
</paragraph>
